Klaviyo uses cursor-based pagination. All list responses include:
```json
{
  "data": [...],
  "links": {
    "self": "https://a.klaviyo.com/api/profiles?page[size]=100",
    "next": "https://a.klaviyo.com/api/profiles?page[size]=100&page[cursor]=WzE2MjQ..."
  }
}
```
`links.next` is `null` when there are no more pages. The connector extracts the `page[cursor]` query param from the next URL via `_extract_cursor()`.

Klaviyo returns errors in JSON:API format:
```json
{
  "errors": [
    {
      "id": "...",
      "status": "401",
      "code": "not_authenticated",
      "title": "Not Authenticated",
      "detail": "The request is not authenticated."
    }
  ]
}
```
The HTTP client extracts `errors[0].detail` (falling back to `errors[0].title`) as the error message.
